****************************************************************************************************
* The Account Management App        
* @author dbernstein@duraspace.org
****************************************************************************************************

To run, execute:  
    mvn jetty:run
and open http://localhost:9000/ama in your browser.

To use an alternate port use -Djetty.port option. This will update the port that jetty starts on,
as well as the port that the unit tests connect to (see: src/test/resources/test-ama.properties).

If you wish to run the jetty server  a port
other than the default:9000, you must specify the jetty port with a command line property:
    mvn -Djetty.port=9991 clean install;

****************************************************************************************************
* Notes on Running Integration Tests
****************************************************************************************************
You might need to install the following packages if you want the selenium tests to work:

sudo apt-get install firefox 
sudo apt-get install xvfb
sudo apt-get install xauth
sudo apt-get install xfonts-base

To run the tests you must enable the selenium test profile: 

mvn clean install -Pprofile-selenium

To run a single selenium test you must start the jetty server in one console, the selenium server
in another and the test run in yet a third.

Console #1: mvn jetty:run
Console #2: mvn selenium:start-server
Console #3: mvn test -Pprofile-selenium -Dtest=<YourTestNameHere>


To debug a single test in eclipse,  just follow the above steps for consoles #1 and #2 and run the
test of choice in Eclipse or the IDE of choice.

****************************************************************************************************
* Eclipse Users
****************************************************************************************************
To generate project and classpath files for eclipse, simply run the following from the project root:

mvn eclipse:eclipse -DdownloadSources=true -DdownloadJavadocs=true
